    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25a.86-88_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8<del>7</del><add>6</add></fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>5-27-58</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have learned from Dorothy Stout that Mrs. Neihardt died from injuries suffered in an automobile accident. I was quite troubled on hearing the sad news.</p>
                
                <p>My concern is more for you than for your wife, although I will miss her keenly. But she is safe in port, while you must face the storms alone. Of course, you have God with you, and you have countless friends and admirers. But, no doubt, you feel alone.</p>
                
                <p>You will have my prayers, Dr. Neihardt, although I don't
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.86-88_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="authorial">2</fw>
                <fw type="curatorial">8<del>8</del><add>7</add></fw>
                
                    know anybody who could bring up more reserves of strength <add>than you.</add> You have counseled me and strengthened me in the past; this is the best chance I'll have to repay you.</p>
                
                <p>Remember how you and Mrs. Neihardt told me I needed a wife near my own age? I enjoyed those quiet, intimate discussions; they were all too brief.</p>
                
                <p>You were partial to Dorothy, of course. We have become really close yet but, after some puzzling setbacks, I seem to be closing ground. Wish me luck and pray for me.</p>
                
                <p>I'm working as a salesmen, saving toward my master's work.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Best wishes,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Odell Williams</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
